    "english":
        "Allāhumma innī `abduk,  ibnu `abdik,  ibnu amatik,  nāsiyatī biyadik,  māḍin fiyya ḥukmuk, `adlun fiyya qaḍā'uk,  as'aluka bikullis’min huwa lak,  sammayta bihi nafsak,  aw anzaltahu fī kitābik,  aw `allamtahu aḥadan min khalqik,  aw‘ista'tharta bihi fī `ilmil-ghaybi `indak, an taj`ala ‘l-Qur'āna rabī`a qalbī,  wa nūra ṣadrī,  wa jalā'a ḥuznī,  wa dhahāba hammī.\n\n O Allah, I am Your slave, and the son of Your male slave, and the son of your female slave.  My forehead is in Your Hand (i.e. you have control over me).  Your Judgment upon me is assured, and Your Decree concerning me is just.  I ask You by every Name that You have named Yourself with,  revealed in Your Book,  taught any one of Your creation,  or kept unto Yourself in the knowledge of the unseen that is with You,  to make the Qur'an the spring of my heart, and the light of my chest, the banisher of my sadness, and the reliever of my distress.\n\nReference: Ahmad 1/391, and Al-Albani graded it authentic. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For anxiety and sorrow",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 121",
    "arabic":
        " اللّهُـمَّ إِنِّي أَعْوذُ بِكَ مِنَ الهَـمِّ وَ الْحُـزْنِ، والعًجْـزِ والكَسَلِ والبُخْـلِ والجُـبْنِ، وضَلْـعِ الـدَّيْنِ وغَلَبَـةِ الرِّجال",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma 'innī 'a`ūdhu bika  mina ‘l-ḥammi wa ‘l-ḥuzn,  wa ‘l-`ajzi wa ‘l-kasal,  wa ‘l-bukhli wa ‘l-jubn,  wa ḍala`id-dayn,  wa ghalabatir-rijāl.\n\n O Allah, I seek refuge in you from grief and sadness, from weakness and from laziness, from miserliness and from cowardice, from being overcome by debt and overpowered by men (i.e. others).\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari 7/158. See also Al-Asqalani, Fathul-Bari 11/173. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For one in distress",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 122",
    "arabic":
        " لَا إلَهَ إِلَّا اللَّهُ الْعَظـيمُ الْحَلِـيمْ، لَا إِلَهَ إِلَّا اللَّهُ  رَبُّ العَـرْشِ العَظِيـمِ، لَا إِلَـهَ إِلَّا اللَّهْ رَبُّ السَّمَـوّاتِ ورّبُّ الأَرْضِ ورَبُّ العَرْشِ الكَـريم",
    "english":
        "Lā ilāha illallāh al-`Aẓīmul-Ḥalīm,  lā ilāha illallāh Rabbu ‘l-`Arshi ‘l-'Aẓīm,  lā ilāha illallāh Rabbus-samāwāti wa Rabbu ‘l-arḍ  wa Rabbu ‘l-`Arshi ‘l-Karīm.\n\n There is none worthy of worship but Allah,  the Mighty, the Forbearing.  There is none worthy of worship but Allah, Lord of the Magnificent Throne.  There is none worthy of worship but Allah, Lord of the heavens and Lord of the earth,  and Lord of the Noble Throne.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari 8/154, Muslim 4/2092 "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For one in distress",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 123",
    "arabic":
        " اللّهُـمَّ رَحْمَتَـكَ أَرْجـو  فَلا تَكِلـني إِلى نَفْـسي طَـرْفَةَ عَـيْن،  وَأَصْلِـحْ لي شَأْنـي كُلَّـه  لَا إِلَهَ إِلَّا أنْـت",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma raḥmataka arjū  falā takilnī ilā nafsī ṭarfata `ayn,  wa aṣliḥ lī sha'nī kullah,  lā ilāha illā ant.\n\n O Allah, I hope for Your mercy.  Do not leave me to myself even for the blinking of an eye (i.e. a moment).  Correct all of my affairs for me.  There is none worthy of worship but You.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 4/324, Ahmad 5/42. Al-Albani graded it as good in Sahih Abu Dawud  3/959. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For one in distress",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 124",
    "arabic":
        " لَا إِلَهَ إِلَّا أنْـت سُـبْحانَكَ إِنِّي كُنْـتُ مِنَ الظّـالِميـن",
    "english":
        "Lā ilāha illā anta subḥānaka  innī kuntu minaẓ-ẓālimīn.\n\n There is none worthy of worship but You, glory is to You.  Surely, I was among the wrongdoers.\n\nReference: At-Tirmidhi 5/529. Al-Hakim declared it authentic and Ath-Thahabi agreed  with him 1/ 505. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmidhi 3/168. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For one in distress",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 125",
    "arabic": " اللهُ اللهُ رَبِّي لا أُشْـرِكُ بِهِ شَيْـئاً",
    "english":
        "Allāh, Allāhu Rabbī lā ushriku bihi shay'a.\n\nAllah, Allah is my Lord. I do not associate anything with Him.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 2/87. See also Al-Albani, Sahih Ibn Mdjah 2/335. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon encountering an enemy or those of authority",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 126",
    "arabic":
        " اللّهُـمَّ إِنا نَجْـعَلُكَ في نُحـورِهِـم، وَنَعـوذُ بِكَ مِنْ شُرورِهـمْ",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma innā naj`aluka fī nuḥūrihim  wa na`ūdhu bika min shurūrihim.\n\n O Allah, we ask You to restrain them by their necks, and we seek refuge in You from their evil.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 2/89, and Al-Hakim graded it authentic and Ath-Thahabi agreed  2/142. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon encountering an enemy or those of authority",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 127",
    "arabic":
        " اللّهُـمَّ أَنْتَ عَضُـدي، وَأَنْتَ نَصـيري، بِكَ أَجـولُ وَبِكَ أَصـولُ وَبِكَ أُقـاتِل",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma anta `aḍudī, wa anta naṣīrī,  bika ajūlu, wa bika aṣūlu, wa bika uqātil.\n\n O Allah, You are my strength and You are my support.  For Your sake, I go forth and for Your sake, I advance and for Your sake, I fight.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 3/42, At-Tirmidhi 5/572. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmidhi  3/183. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon encountering an enemy or those of authority",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 128",
    "arabic": " حَسْبُـنا اللهُ وَنِعْـمَ الوَكـيل",
    "english":
        "Ḥasbunallāhu wa ni`mal-wakīl.\n\nAllah is sufficient for us and the best of those on whom to depend.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, 5/172. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For one afraid of the ruler's injustice",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 129",
    "arabic":
        " اللَّهُمَّ ربَّ السَّمَوَاتِ السَّبْعِ، وَرَبَّ الْعَرْشِ الْعَظِيمِ،  كُنْ لِي جَاراً مِنْ فُلاَنِ بْنِ فُلاَنٍ، وَأَحْزَابِهِ مِنْ خَلاَئِقِكَ، أَنْ يَفْرُطَ عَلَيَّ أَحَدٌ مِنْهُمْ أَوْ يَطْغَى، عَزَّ جَارُكَ، وَجَلَّ ثَنَاؤُكَ، وَلاَ إِلَهَ إِلاَّ أَنْتَ",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma Rabbas-samāwātis-sab`,  wa Rabba ‘l-`Arshi ‘l-`Aẓīm,  kun lī jāran min [here you mention the person's name],  wa aḥzābihi min khalā'iqik,  an yafruṭa `alayya aḥadun minhum aw yaṭghā,  `azza jāruk,  wa jalla thanā'uk,  wa lā ilāha illā ant.\n\n O Allah, Lord of the seven heavens,  Lord of the Magnificent Throne,  be for me a support against [such and such a person] and his helpers from among your creatures,  lest any of them abuse me or do me wrong. Mighty is Your patronage, and glorious are Your praises. There is none worthy of worship but You.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, Al-'Adab Al-Mufrad (no. 707). Al-Albani graded it authentic in  Sahih Al-'Adab Al-Mufrad (no. 545). "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For one afraid of the ruler's injustice",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 130",
    "arabic":
        " الله أكبر، الله أعز من خلقه جميعاً ، الله أعز مما أخاف وأحذر ، أعوذ بالله الذي لا إله إلا هو ، الممسك السموات السبع  أن يقعن على الأرض إلا بإذنه ، من شر عبدك فلان ، وجنوده وأتباعه وأشياعه ، من الجن والأنس ، اللهم كن لي جاراً من شرهم ، جل ثناؤك وعز جارك ،  وتبارك اسمك ،  ولا إله غيرك (ثلاث مرات)",
    "english":
        "Allāhu Akbar,  Allāhu a`azzu min khalqihi jamī`a,  Allāhu a`azzu mimmā akhāfu wa aḥdhar,  a`ūdhu billāhi ‘l-ladhī lā ilāha illā hū, almumsikis-samāwātis-sab`i   an yaqa`na `ala ‘l-arḍi illā bi idhnih, min sharri `abdika [name of the person],  wa junūdihi wa atbā`ihi wa ashyā`ih,  mina ‘l-jinni wa ‘l-ins,  Allāhumma kun lī jāran min sharrihim, jalla thanā'uk, wa `azza jāruk, wa tabāraka-smuk,  wa lā ilāha ghayruk.\n\n Allah is the Most Great,  Mightier than all His creation.  He is Mightier than what I fear and dread.  I seek refuge in Allah, Who there is none worthy of worship but Him.  He is the One Who holds the seven heavens from falling upon the earth except by His command.  [I seek refuge in You Allah] from the evil of Your slave [name of the person],  and his helpers, his followers, and his supporters from among the jinn and mankind. O Allah, be my support against their evil. Glorious are Your praises and mighty is Your patronage. Blessed is Your Name, there is no true God but You. (Recite three times in Arabic.)\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, 5/172. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Against enemies",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 131",
    "arabic":
        " اللَّهُمَّ مُنْزِلَ الْكِتَاب سَرِيعَ الْحِسَاب اهْزِم الأَحْزَاب اللَّهُمَّ اهْزِمْهُمْ وَ زَلْزِلْهُم",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma munzila ‘l-kitāb,  sarī`a ‘l-ḥisāb,  ihzimi ‘l-aḥzāb,  Allāhumma-hzimhum wa zalzilhum.\n\n O Allah, Revealer of the Book,  Swift to account,  defeat the groups (of disbelievers).  O Allah, defeat them and shake them.\n\nReference: Muslim 3/1362. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: When being afraid of a group of people",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 132",
    "arabic": " اللَّهُمَّ اكْفِنِيهِم بمَا شِئْت",
    "english":
        "Allāhummak-finīhim bimā shi't.\n\n O Allah, suffice (i.e. protect) me against them however You wish.\n\nReference: Muslim 4/2300. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For one afflicted with doubt in his faith",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 133",
    "arabic": " يَسْتَعِيذُ بِاللَّهِ. يَنْتَهِي عَمَّا شك فِيهِ.",
    "english":
        "A`ūdhu billāh\n\n(Say:) I seek refuge in Allah.  (Then you should desist from doing what you are in doubt about.)\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, cf. Al-Asqalani, Fathul-Bari 6/336, Muslim 1/120. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For one afflicted with doubt in his faith",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 134",
    "arabic": " يقول\" آمنت بالله ورسله\"",
    "english":
