    "english":
        "Huwa ‘l-Awwalu wa ‘l-Ākhir, waẓ-Ẓāhiru wal-Bāṭin,  wa huwa bikulli shay'in `Alīm.\n\n(Recite the Ayat) He is the First and the Last,  the Most High and the Most Near.  And He is the Knower of all things (in Arabic).\n\nReference: Al-Hadid 57:3, Abu Dawud 4/329. Al-Albani graded it good in SahihAbu Dawud,  3/962. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Settling a debt",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 136",
    "arabic":
        " اللّهُـمَّ اكْفِـني بِحَلالِـكَ عَنْ حَـرامِـك، وَأَغْنِـني بِفَضْـلِكِ عَمَّـنْ سِـواك",
    "english":
        "Allāhummak-finī biḥalālika `an ḥarāmik,  wa 'aghninī bi faḍlika `amman siwāk.\n\n O Allah, suffice me with what You have allowed instead of what You have forbidden,  and make me independent of all others besides You.\n\nReference: At-Tirmidhi 5/560. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmidhi 3/180. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Settling a debt",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 137",
    "arabic":
        " اللَّهُمَّ إِنِّي أَعُوذُ بِكَ مِنَ الْهَمِّ وَالْحَزَنِ، وَالْعَجْزِ وَالْكَسَلِ، وَالْبُخْلِ وَالْجُبْنِ، وَضَلَعِ الدَّيْنِ وَغَلَبَةِ الرِّجَالِ",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma innī a`ūdhu bika mina ‘l-ḥammi wa ‘l-ḥazan,  wa ‘l-`ajzi wa ‘l-kasal, wa ‘l-bukhli wa ‘l-jubn,  wa ḍala`id-dayni wa ghalabatir-rijāl.\n\n O Allah! I seek refuge with You from worry and grief, from incapacity and laziness, from cowardice and miserliness, from being heavily in debt and from being overpowered by (other) men.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari 7/158. "
  },
  {
    "title":
        "Chapter: For one afflicted by whisperings in prayer or recitation",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 138",
    "arabic":
        " أَعُوذُ بِاللَّهِ مِنَ الشَّيطَانِ الرَّجِيمِ،  وَاتْفُلْ عَلَى يَسَارِكَ (ثلاثاً)",
    "english":
        "A`ūdhu billāhi minash-shayṭānir-rajīm.\n\n(Say:) I seek refuge in Allah from Satan the outcast  (then blow with a little spittle to your left).  (Do this three times reciting in Arabic.)\n\nReference: Muslim 4/1729. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For one whose affairs have become difficult",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 139",
    "arabic":
        " اللَّهُمَّ لاَ سَهْلَ إِلاَّ مَا جَعَلْتَهُ سَهْلاً، وَأَنْتَ تَجْعَلُ الْحَزْنَ إِذَا شِئْتَ سَهْلاً",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma lā saḥla illā ma ja`altahu saḥla  wa anta taj`alu ‘l-ḥazna idhā shi'ta saḥla.\n\n O Allah, there is no ease other than what You make easy.  If You please You ease sorrow.\n\nReference: Ibn Hibban in his Sahih (no. 2427), and Ibn As- Sunni (no. 351). Al-Hafidh  (Ibn Hajar) said that this Hadith is authentic. It was also declared  authentic by 'Abdul-Qadir Al-Arna'ut in his checking of An-Nawawi's  Kitabul-Athkarp. 106. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon committing a sin",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 140",
    "arabic":
        " مَا مِنْ عَبْدٍ يُذنِبُ ذَنْباً فَيُحْسِنُ الطُّهُورَ، ثُمَّ يَقُومُ فَيُصَلِّي رَكْعَتَيْنِ، ثُمَّ يَسْتَغْفِرُ اللَّهَ إِلاَّ غَفَرَ اللَّهُ لَهُ",
    "english":
        "There is not any slave of Allah who commits a sin, then he perfects his purification and stands to pray two Rak'ahs of prayer, then seeks Allah's forgiveness, except that Allah will forgive him.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 2/86, At-Tirmidhi 2/257. Al-Albani graded it authentic in Sahih  Abu Dawud 1/283. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For expelling the devil and his whisperings",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 141",
    "arabic": " الاستعاذة بالله منه",
    "english":
        "A`ūdhu billāhi minash-shayṭānir-rajīm.\n\nSeeking refuge with Allah against him (i.e. by saying I seek refuge in Allah from Satan the outcast).\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 1/206, At-Tirmidhi. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmidhi 1/77,  and Surat Al-Mu'minun, 23:98-9. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For expelling the devil and his whisperings",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 142",
    "arabic": " الْأَذَانُ",
    "english":
        "--\n\nThe call to prayer - 'Athan.\n\nReference: Muslim 1/291, Al-Bukhari 1/151. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For expelling the devil and his whisperings",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 143",
    "arabic": " الْأَذْكَارُ وَقِرَاءَةُ الْقُرْآنِ",
    "english":
        "--\n\nSaying words of Allah's remembrance (Thikr) and recitation of the Qur'an.\n\nReference: \"Do not turn your homes into graveyards, surely the Devil flees from the  house in which Surat Al-Baqarah is read,\" Muslim 1/539. The Devil is also  driven out by the invocations for morning and evening, those that are said  before sleeping and upon waking up, those for entering and leaving the  house, including those for entering and leaving the mosque, and by many  other authentic invocations taught to us by the Prophet (ﷺ) such as the  reading of 'Ayatul-Kursi, (Al-Baqarah 2:255), and the last two 'Ayat of  Surat Al-Baqarah before going to sleep. Whoever says: \"There is none worthy  of worship but Allah alone, Who has no partner, His is the dominion and His  is the praise, and he is Able to do all things,\" one hundred times, it will  be a protection for him from the Devil throughout the day.' "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: When stricken with a mishap or overtaken by an affair",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 144",
    "arabic": " قَدَّرَ اللهُ وَما شـاءَ فَعَـل",
    "english":
        "Qaddarallāhu wa mā shā'a fa`al.\n\nIt is the Decree of Allah and He does whatever He wills.\n\nReference: \"The strong believer is better and more dear to Allah than the weak  believer, and in each of them there is good. Be vigilant for what is to  your benefit and seek the help of Allah and do not falter. But when you are  striken by some setback, do not say: 'If only I had done such and such,'  rather say: 'It is the Decree of Allah and He does whatever He wills.' For  verily the saying 'if (i.e. if only I had) begins the work of the Devil.\"  Muslim 4/2052. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Congratulation on the occasion of a birth and its reply",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 145",
    "arabic":
        " (بَارَكَ اللَّهُ لَكَ فِي الْمَوْهُوبِ لَكَ،  وَشَكَرْتَ الْوَاهِبَ،  وَبَلَغَ أَشُدَّهُ،  وَرُزِقْتَ بِرَّهُ).    وَيَرُدُّ عَلَيْهِ الْمُهَــــــنَّأُ فَيَقُولُ: (بَارَكَ اللَّهُ لَكَ وَبَارَكَ عَلَيْكَ،  وَجَزَاكَ اللَّهُ خَيْراً،  وَرَزَقَكَ اللَّهُ مِثْلَهُ،  وَأَجْزَلَ ثَوَابَكَ).",
    "english":
        "Bārakallāhu laka fi ‘l-mawhūbi lak,  wa shakarta ‘l-wāhib,  wa balagha ashuddah,  wa ruziqta birrah.\n\nThe reply of the person being congratulated is to say:\n\nBārakallahu laka wa bāraka `alayk,  wa jazākallāhu khayra,  wa razaqakallāhu mithlah,  wa ajzala thawābak.\n\n May Allah bless you with His gift to you,  and may you (the new parent) give thanks, may the child reach the maturity of years, and may you be granted its righteousness. \n\nThe reply of the person being congratulated is to say:\n\nMay Allah bless you, and shower His blessings upon you,  and may Allah reward you well and bestow upon you its like  and reward you abundantly\n\nReference: An-Nawawi, Kitdbul-'Athkarp. 349, and Sahihul-'Athkar2/7l3 by Saleem  Al-Hilali. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Placing childen under Allah’s protection",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 146",
    "arabic":
        " كان رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم يعوذ الحسن والحسين \" أعيذكما بكلمات الله التامة ، من كل شيطان وهامة ،  ومن كل عينِ لامة \"",
    "english":
        "The Prophet (ﷺ) used to seek Allah's protection for Al-Hasan and Al-Husain by saying:\n\nU`īthukumā bikalimāti ‘llāhit-tāmmati  min kulli shayṭānin wa hāmmah,  wa min kulli `aynin lāmmah\n\n I seek protection for you in the Perfect Words of Allah  from every devil and every beast,  and from every envious blameworthy eye.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari4/119. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: When visiting the sick",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 147",
    "arabic": " لا بأْسَ طَهـورٌ إِنْ شـاءَ الله",
    "english":
        "Lā ba'sa ṭahūrun in shā Allāh.\n\nDo not worry, it will be a purification (for you), Allah willing.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, cf. Al-Asqalani Fathul-Bari 10/118. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: When visiting the sick",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 148",
    "arabic":
