    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 168",
    "arabic":
        " سُبْـحانَ الّذي يُسَبِّـحُ الـرَّعْدُ بِحَمْـدِهِ، وَالملائِكـةُ مِنْ خيـفَته",
    "english":
        "Subḥāna ‘l-ladhī yusabbiḥur-ra`du bi ḥamdihi  wa ‘l-malā'ikatu min khīfatih.\n\n Glory is to Him Whom thunder and angels glorify due to fear of Him.\n\nReference: Whenever Abdullah bin Zubair (RA) would hear thunder, he would abandon all  conversation and say this supplication. See Al-Muwatta' 2/992. It was  graded authentic by Al-Albani as a statement of Abdullah bin Zubayr only. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For rain",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 169",
    "arabic":
        " اللّهُمَّ اسْقِـنا غَيْـثاً مُغيـثاً مَريئاً مُريـعاً، نافِعـاً غَيْـرَ ضار، عاجِـلاً غَـيْرَ آجِل",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma ‘asqinā ghaythan mughīthan marī'an murī`a,  nāfi`an ghayra ḍārr,  `ājilan ghayra ājil.\n\nO Allah, shower upon us abundant rain, beneficial not harmful, swiftly and not delayed.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 1/303. See also Al-Albani SahihAbu Dawud 1/216. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For rain",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 170",
    "arabic": " اللّهُمَّ أغِثْنـا،  اللّهُمَّ أغِثْنـا،  اللّهُمَّ أغِثْنـا",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma aghithnā,  Allāhumma aghithnā,  Allāhumma aghithnā.\n\n O Allah, send us rain.  O Allah, send us rain.  O Allah, send us rain.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari 1/224, Muslim 2/613. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For rain",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 171",
    "arabic":
        " اللّهُمَّ اسْقِ عِبادَكَ وَبَهـائِمَك،  وَانْشُـرْ رَحْمَـتَكَ  وَأَحْيِي بَلَـدَكَ المَيِّـت",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma’sqi `ibādaka wa bahā'imak,  wanshur raḥmatak,  wa aḥyi baladaka ‘l-mayyit\n\n O Allah, give water to Your slaves, and Your livestock,  and spread Your mercy,  and revive Your dead land.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 1/305. Al-Albani graded it good in Sahih Abu Dawud 1/218. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: When it rains",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 172",
    "arabic": " اللّهُمَّ صَيِّـباً نافِـعاً",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma ṣayyiban nāfi`a.\n\nO Allah, (bring) beneficial rain clouds.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, cf. Al-Asqalani, Fathul-Bari 2/518. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: After rainfall",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 173",
    "arabic": " مُطِـرْنا بِفَضْـلِ اللهِ وَرَحْمَـتِه",
    "english":
        "Muṭirnā bifaḍlillāhi wa raḥmatih.\n\nWe have been given rain by the grace and mercy of Allah. \n\nReference: Al-Bukhari 1/205, Muslim 1/83. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Asking for clear skies",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 174",
    "arabic":
        " اللّهُمَّ حَوالَيْنا وَلا عَلَيْـنا، اللّهُمَّ عَلى الآكـامِ وَالظِّـراب،  وَبُطـونِ الأوْدِية، وَمَنـابِتِ الشَّجـر",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma ḥawālaynā wa lā `alaynā.  Allāhumma `ala ‘l-ākāmi waẓ-ẓirāb,  wa buṭūni ‘l-awdiyati, wa manābitish-shajar.\n\n O Allah, let the rain fall around us and not upon us,  O Allah, (let it fall) on the pastures, hills, valleys, and the roots of trees.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari 1/224, Muslim 1/614 "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon sighting the crescent moon",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 175",
    "arabic":
        " اللهُ أَكْـبَر، اللّهُمَّ أَهِلَّـهُ عَلَيْـنا بِالأمْـنِ وَالإيمـان، والسَّلامَـةِ والإسْلام، وَالتَّـوْفيـقِ لِما تُحِـبُّ رَبَّنـا وَتَـرْضـى،  رَبُّنـا وَرَبُّكَ الله",
    "english":
        "Allāhu Akbar,  Allāhumma ahillahu `alayna bi ‘l-amni wa ‘l-īmān, was-salāmati wa ‘l-'Islām,  wat-tawfīqi limā tuḥibbu Rabbanā wa tarḍā,  Rabbunā wa Rabbukallāh.\n\n Allah is the Most Great.  O Allah, bring us the new moon with security and Faith,  with peace and in Islam,  and in harmony with what our Lord loves and what pleases Him.  Our Lord and your Lord is Allah.\n\nReference: At-Tirmidhi 5/504, Ad-Darimi 1/336. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmidhi  3/157. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon breaking fast",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 176",
    "arabic":
        " ذَهَـبَ الظَّمَـأُ، وَابْتَلَّـتِ العُـروق، وَثَبَـتَ الأجْـرُ إِنْ شـاءَ الله",
    "english":
        "Dhahabaẓ-ẓama',  wabtallati ‘l-`urūq,  wa thabata ‘l-'ajru in shā Allāh.\n\n The thirst is gone, the veins are moistened,  and the reward is confirmed, if Allah wills.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 2/306 and others. See also Al- Albani, Sahihul-Jami' As-Saghir  4/209. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon breaking fast",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 177",
    "arabic":
        " اللّهُـمَّ إِنَّـي أَسْـأَلُـكَ بِرَحْمَـتِكَ الّتي وَسِـعَت كُلَّ شيء،  أَنْ تَغْـفِرَ لي",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma innī as'aluka  bi raḥmatika ‘l-latī wasi`at kulla shay'  an taghfira lī.\n\n O Allah, I ask You by Your mercy, which encompasses all things, that You forgive me.\n\nReference: Ibn Majah 1/557 from a supplication of Abdullah bin 'Amr. Al-Hafidh graded  it as good in his checking of An-Nawawi's Kitabul-'Athkdr. See Sharhul-  Athkar 4/342. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Before eating",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 178",
    "arabic":
        " إِذَا أَكَلَ أَحَدُكُمْ طَعَاماً فَلْيَقُلْ  بِسْمِ اللَّهِ، فَإِنْ نَسِيَ فِي أَوَّلِهِ فَلْيَقُلْ  بسمِ اللَّهِ فِي أَوَّلِهِ وَآخِرِهِ",
    "english":
        "When anyone of you begins eating, say: Bismillāh. And if you forget then when you remember, say: Bismillāhi fī awwalihi wa ākhirih.\n\n When anyone of you begins eating, say:\n\nWith the Name of Allah.\n\nAnd if you forget then, when you remember, say:\n\nWith the Name of Allah, in the beginning, and in the end.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 3/347, At-Tirmidhi 4/288. See Al- Albani's Sahih At-Tirmidhi  2/167. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Before eating",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 179",
    "arabic":
        " مَنْ أَطْعَمَهُ اللَّهُ الطَّعَامَ فَلْيَقُلْ: \"اللَّهُمَّ بَارِكْ لَنَا فِيهِ وَأَطْعِمْنَا خَيْراً مِنْهُ\"، وَمَنْ سَقَاهُ اللَّهُ لَبَناً فَلْيَقُلْ \"اللَّهُمَّ بَارِكْ لَنَا فِيهِ وَزِدْنَا مِنْهُ\"",
    "english":
        "Whomever Allah has given food, should say: Allāhumma bārik lanā fīhi, wa aṭ`imnā khayran minh.\n\nWhomever Allah has given milk to drink, should say : Allāhumma bārik lanā fīhi, wa zidnā minh.\n\n Whomever Allah has given food, should say:\n\nO Allah, bless us in it and provide us with better than it.\n\nWhomever Allah has given milk to drink, should say :\n\nO Allah, bless us in it and give us more of it.\n\nReference: At-Tirmidhi 5/506. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmidhi 3/158. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon completing the meal",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 180",
    "arabic":
        " الْحَمْـدُ للهِ الَّذي أَطْعَمَنـي هـذا وَرَزَقَنـيهِ مِنْ غَـيْرِ حَوْلٍ مِنِّي وَلا قُوَّة",
    "english":
        "Alhamdu lillāhi ‘l-ladhī aṭ`amanī hādhā,  wa razaqanīhi min ghayri ḥawlin minnī wa lā quwwah.\n\n Praise is to Allah Who has given me this food,  and sustained me with it though I was unable to do it and powerless.\n\nReference: At-Tirmidhi, Abu Dawud, and Ibn Majah. See also Al-Albani, Sahih  At-Tirmidhi 3/159. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon completing the meal",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 181",
    "arabic":
        " الْحَمْـدُ للهِ حَمْـداً كَثـيراً طَيِّـباً مُبـارَكاً فيه، غَيْرَ مَكْفِيٍّ وَلا مُوَدَّعٍ وَلا مُسْتَغْـنىً عَنْـهُ رَبَّـنا",
    "english":
        "Alhamdu lillāhi ḥamdan kathīran tayyiban mubārakan fīh,  ghayra makfiyyin wa lā muwadda`in,  wa lā mustaghnan `anhu Rabbanā.\n\n All praise is to Allah, praise in abundance, good and blessed. It cannot [be compensated for, nor can it] be left, nor can it be done without, our Lord.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari 6/214, At-Tirmidhi 5/507. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Of the guest for the host",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 182",
    "arabic":
        " اللّهُـمَّ بارِكْ لَهُمْ فيما رَزَقْـتَهُم،  وَاغْفِـرْ لَهُـمْ وَارْحَمْهُمْ",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma bārik lahum fī mā razaqtahum,  wagh’fir lahum warḥamhum.\n\n O Allah, bless them in what You have provided for them,  and forgive them and have mercy on them.\n\nReference: Muslim 3/1615. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: To one who intends to give food or drink",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 183",
    "arabic": " اللّهُـمَّ أَطْعِمْ مَن أَطْعَمَني،  وَاسْقِ مَن سقاني",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma aṭ`im man aṭ`amanī  wasqi man saqānī.\n\n O Allah, feed the one who has fed me, and give drink to the one who has given me drink.\n\nReference: Muslim 3/126. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: When breaking fast in someone’s home",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 184",
    "arabic":
        " أَفْطَـرَ عِنْدَكُم الصّـائِمونَ وَأَكَلَ طَعامَـكُمُ الأبْـرار، وَصَلَّـتْ عَلَـيْكُمُ الملائِكَـة",
    "english":
        "Afṭara `indakumuṣ-ṣā'imūn,  wa akala ṭa`āmakumu ‘l-'abrār,  wa ṣallat `alaykumu ‘l-malā'ikah.\n\n With you, those who are fasting have broken their fast,  you have fed those who are righteous,  and the angels recite their prayers upon you.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 3/367, Ibn Majah 1/556, An-Nasa'i, 'Amalul-Yawm wal-Laylah 296-8.  Al-Albani graded it authentic in Sahih Abu Dawud 2/730. "
  },
  {
    "title":
        "Chapter: By one fasting when presented with food and does not break his fast",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 185",
    "arabic":
        " (إِذَا دُعِيَ أَحَدُكُمْ فَلْيُجِبْ، فَإِنْ كَانَ صَائِماً فَلْيُصَلِّ، وَإِنْ كَانَ مُفْطِراً فَلْيَطْعَمْ) ، وَمَعْنَى فَلْيُصَلِّ أَيْ فَلْيَدْعُ.",
    "english":
        "--\n\nWhen you are invited (to eat) then reply to the invitation.  If you are fasting then invoke Allah's blessings (on your host),  and if you are not fasting then eat.\n\nReference: Muslim 2/1054. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: When insulted while fasting",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 186",
    "arabic": " إِنِّي صَائِمٌ،  إِنِّي صَائِمٌ",
    "english":
        "Innī  ṣā'im, innī  ṣā'im.\n\n I am fasting.  I am fasting.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, cf. Al-Asqalani, Fathul-BAri 4/103, Muslim 2/806. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon seeing the early or premature fruit",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 187",
    "arabic":
        " اللّهُـمَّ بارِكْ لَنا في ثَمَـرِنا، وَبارِكْ لَنا في مَدينَتِنـا، وَبارِكْ لَنا في صاعِنـا، وَبارِكْ لَنا في مُدِّنا",
    "english":
        "Allahumma bārik lanā fī thamarinā,  wa bārik lanā fī madīnatinā  wa bārik lanā fī  ṣā`inā,  wa bārik lanā fī muddinā.\n\n O Allah, bless us in our dates and bless us in our town,  bless us in our Sa' and in our Mudd.\n\nReference: Muslim 2/1000 (Sa' and Mudd are both dry measures used for agricultural  produce by the Arabs in the Prophet's time. Of the two, the So.' was the  larger measure.) (Translator) "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon sneezing",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 188",
    "arabic":
        " إِذَا عَطَسَ أَحَدُكُم فَلْيَقُلِ (الْحَمْدُ لِلَّهِ)، وَلْيَقُلْ لَهُ أَخُوهُ أَوْ صَاحِبُهُ: (يَرْحَمُكَ اللَّهُ)، فَإِذَا قَالَ لَهُ: (يَرحَمُكَ اللَّهُ)، فَلْيَقُلْ: (يَهْدِيكُمُ اللَّهُ وَيُصْلِحُ بَالَكُمْ)",
    "english":
        "When you sneeze , then say : Alḥamdulillāh\n\nYour companion should say : Yarḥamukallāh\n\nWhen someone says Yarḥamukallāh to you then you should say: Yahdīkumu ‘llāhu wa yuṣliḥu bālakum.\n\nWhen you sneeze, then say: All praises and thanks are to Allah.\n\nYour companion should say: May Allah have mercy upon you.\n\nWhen someone says Yarḥamukallāh to you then you should say: May Allah guide you and set your affairs in order.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari 7/125. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: When a disbeliever praises Allah after sneezing",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 189",
    "arabic": " يَهْـديكُـمُ اللهُ وَيُصْـلِحُ بالَـكُم",
    "english":
        "Yahdīkumullāhu wa yuṣliḥu bālakum.\n\nMay Allah guide you and set your affairs in order\n\nReference: At-Tirmidhi 5/82, Ahmad 4/400, Abu Dawud 4/ 308. See also Al-Albani, Sahih  At-Tirmidhi 2/354. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: To the newlywed",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 190",
    "arabic":
        " بارَكَ اللّهُ لَك،  وَبارَكَ عَلَـيْك،  وَجَمَعَ بَيْـنَكُما في خَـيْر",
    "english":
        "Bārakallāhu lak,  wa bāraka `alayk,  wa jama`a baynakumā fī khayr.\n\n May Allah bless you, and shower His blessings upon you,  and join you together in goodness.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud, Ibn Majah and At-Tirmidhi. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmidhi  1/316. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: On the wedding night or when buying an animal",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 191",
    "arabic":
        " إِذَا تَزَوَّجَ أَحَدُكُمُ امْرَأَةً، أَوْ إِذَا اشْتَرَى خَادِماً فَلْيَقُلْ:  (اللَّهُمَّ إِنِّي أَسْأَلُكَ خَيْرَهَا،  وَخَيْرَ مَا جَبَلْتَهَا عَلَيْهِ،  وَأَعُوذُ بِكَ مِنْ شَرِّهَا،  وَشَرِّ مَا جَبَلْتَهَا عَلَيْهِ)،  وَإِذَا اشْتَرَى بَعِيراً فَلْيَأْخُذْ بِذِرْوَةِ سَنَامِهِ وَلْيَقُلْ مِثْلَ ذَلِكَ.",
    "english":
        "When any of you marries a woman or purchases a maid-servant then let him say: Allāhumma innī as'aluka khayrahā  wa khayra mā jabaltahā `alayh, wa a`ūdhu bika min sharrihā  wa sharri mā jabaltahā `alayh.\n\n When any of you marries a woman or purchases a maid-servant then let him say :\n\nO Allah, I ask You for the goodness of her, and the goodness upon which You have created her, and I seek refuge in You from the evil of her,  and from the evil upon which You have created her.\n\nIf you purchase a camel then take hold of the top of its hump and say the same.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 2/248 and Ibn Majah 1/617. See also Al-Albani, Sahih Ibn Majah  1/324. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Before sexual intercourse with the wife",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 192",
    "arabic":
        " بِسْمِ الله  اللّهُـمَّ جَنِّبْنا الشَّيْـطانَ،  وَجَنِّبِ الشَّـيْطانَ ما رَزَقْـتَنا",
    "english":
        "Bismillāh.  Allāhumma jannibnash-Shayṭān,  wa jannibish-Shayṭāna mā razaqtanā.\n\n With the Name of Allah.  O Allah, keep the Devil away from us,  and keep the Devil away from that which You provide for us.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari 6/141, Muslim 2/1028. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: When angry",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 193",
    "arabic": " أَعـوذُ بِاللهِ مِنَ الشَّيْـطانِ الرَّجيـم",
    "english":
        "A`ūdhu billāhi minash-Shayṭānir-rajīm.\n\nI seek refuge in Allah from Satan the outcast.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari 7/99, Muslim 4/2015. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon seeing someone in trial or tribulation",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 194",
    "arabic":
        " الْحَمْـدُ للهِ الّذي عافاني مِمّا ابْتَـلاكَ بِهِ، وَفَضَّلَـني عَلى كَثيـرٍ مِمَّنْ خَلَـقَ تَفْضـيلا",
    "english":
        "Alhamdu lillāhi ‘l-ladhī `āfānī mimmab-talāka bihi  wa faḍḍalanī `alā kathīrin mimman khalaqa tafḍīlā.\n\n Praise is to Allah Who has spared me what He has afflicted you with,  and preferred me greatly above much of what He has created.\n\nReference: At-Tirmidhi 5/493,4. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmidhi 3/153. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: At a sitting or gathering",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 195",
    "arabic":
        " عن ابن عمر قال : كان يعد لرسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم في المجلس الواحد مائة مرة من قبل أن يقوم  \"رب اغفر لي  وتب علي  إنك أنت التواب الغفور\"",
    "english":
        "Ibn Umar (ra) said: Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) used to repeat in a single sitting: Rabbigh’fir lī  wa tub `alayy  innaka antat-Tawwābu ‘l-Ghafūr.\n\n Ibn Umar (ra) said: Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) used to repeat in a single sitting:\n\nMy Lord, forgive me, and accept my repentance,  You are the Ever-Relenting, the All-Forgiving.\n\nReference: Sahih Ibn Majah 2/321. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmidhi 3/153. "
  },
  {
    "title":
        "Chapter: For the expiation of sins, said at the conclusion of a sitting or gathering",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 196",
    "arabic":
        " سُبْحـانَكَ اللّهُـمَّ وَبِحَمدِك،  أَشْهَـدُ أَنْ لا إِلهَ إِلاّ أَنْتَ  أَسْتَغْفِرُكَ وَأَتوبُ إِلَـيْك",
    "english":
        "Subhānaka Allāhumma wa biḥamdik,  ash-hadu an lā ilāha illā ant, astaghfiruka wa atību ilayk.\n\n Glory is to You, O Allah, and praise is to You.  I bear witness that there is none worthy of worship but You.  I seek Your forgiveness and repent to You.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud, Ibn Majah, At-Tirmidhi and An-Nasa'i. See also Al-Albani, Sahih  At-Tirmidhi 3/ 153. Aishah (RA) said: \"Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) did not sit  in a gathering, and did not recite the Qur'an, and did not perform any  prayer without concluding by saying ... (then she quoted the above).\" This  was reported by An-Nasa'i in 'Amalul-Yawm wal-Laylah (no.308), and Dr.  Farooq Hamadah graded it authentic in his checking of the same book, p.  273. See also Ahmad 6/77 "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Returning a supplication of forgiveness",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 197",
    "arabic": " وَلَكَ",
    "english":
        "Walaka\n\nAnd you.\n\nReference: Ahmad 5/82, and An-Nasa'i in 'Amalul-Yawm wal-Laylah p. 218, with checking  by Dr. Farooq Hamadah. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: To one who does you a favour",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 198",
    "arabic": " جَزاكَ اللهُ خَـيْراً",
    "english":
        "Jazākallāhu khayra.\n\nMay Allah reward you with good.\n\nReference: At-Tirmidhi (no. 2035). See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmidhi 2/200 and  Sahihul-Jami' (no. 6244). "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Protection from the Dajjal",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 199",
    "arabic":
        " .(مَنْ حَفِظَ عَشْرَ آيَاتٍ مِنْ أَوَّلِ سُورَةِ الْكَهْفِ عُصِمَ مِنَ الدَّجَّالِ) ، وَالْاسْتِعَاذَةُ بِاللَّهِ مِنْ فِتْنَتِهِ عَقِبَ التَّشَهُّدِ الْأَخِيرِ مِنْ كُلِّ صَلاَةٍ.",
    "english":
        "--\n\nWhoever memorizes ten 'Ayat (Verses) from the beginning of Surat Al-Kahf, will be protected from the False Messiah 1  if he recites in every prayer after the final Tashahhud before ending the prayer, seeking the protection of Allah from the trials of the False Messiah.\n\nReference: 1 Muslim 1/555, another version mentions the last ten 'Ayat, Muslim 1/556. 2 See invocations no. 55 and 56 of this book. "
  },
  {
    "title":
        "Chapter: To one who pronounces his love for you, for Allah’s sake",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 200",
    "arabic": " أَحَبَّـكَ الّذي أَحْبَبْـتَني لَه",
    "english":
        "Aḥabbaka ‘lladhī aḥbabtanī lah.\n\nMay He for Whose sake you love me, love you.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 4/333. Al-Albani graded it good in Sahih Abu Dawud 3/965. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: To one who has offered you some of his wealth",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 201",
    "arabic": " بارَكَ اللهُ لَكَ في أَهْلِكَ وَمالِك",
    "english":
        "Bārakallāhu laka fī ahlika wa mālik.\n\nMay Allah bless you in your family and your property.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, cf. Al-Asqalani, Fathul-BAri 4/88. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: To the debtor when his debt is settled",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 202",
    "arabic":
        " بارَكَ اللهُ لَكَ في أَهْلِكَ وَمالِك،  إِنَّما جَـزاءُ السَّلَفِ الْحَمْدُ والأَداء",
    "english":
        "Bārakallāhu laka fī ahlika wa mālik,  innamā jazā'us-salafi ‘l-ḥamdu wa‘l-adā'.\n\n May Allah bless you in your family and your wealth,  surely the reward for a loan is praise and returning (what was borrowed).\n\nReference: An-Nasa'i, 'Amalul-Yawm wal-Laylahp. 300, Ibn Majah 2/809. See also  Al-Albani, Sahih Ibn Majah2/55. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For fear of shirk",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 203",
    "arabic":
        " اللّهُـمَّ إِنّـي أَعـوذُبِكَ أَنْ أُشْـرِكَ بِكَ وَأَنا أَعْـلَمْ،  وَأَسْتَـغْفِرُكَ لِما لا أَعْـلَم",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma innī a`ūdhu bika an ushrika bika wa anā a`lam,  wa astaghfiruka limā lā a`lam.\n\n O Allah, I seek refuge in You lest I associate anything with You knowingly,  and I seek Your forgiveness for what I know not.\n\nReference: Ahmad 4/403. See also Al-Albani, Sahihul-Jami' As-Saghir 3/233 and  Sahihut-Targhib wat- Tarhib 1/19. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: To someone who says \"May Allah bless you\"",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 204",
    "arabic": " وَفيكَ بارَكَ الله",
    "english":
        "Wafīka bārakallāh.\n\nAnd may Allah bless you.\n\nReference: Ibn As-Sunni, p. 138, (no. 278). See also Ibn Al-Qayyim, Al-Wdbil  As-Sayyib, p. 304, with checking by Basheer Muhammad ?Uyoon. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: The scorn of ascribing things to evil omens",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 205",
    "arabic":
        " اللّهُـمَّ لا طَيْـرَ إِلاّ طَيْـرُك،  وَلا خَـيْرَ إِلاّ خَـيْرُك،  وَلا إِلهَ غَيْـرُك",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma lā ṭayra illā ṭayruk,  wa lā khayra illā khayruk,  wa lā ilāha ghayruk.\n\n O Allah there is no portent other than Your portent,  no goodness other than Your goodness,  and none worthy of worship other than You.\n\nReference: Ahmad 2/220, Ibn As-Sunni (no. 292). See also Al-Albani,  Silsilatul-'Ahadlth As-Sahihah 3/54, (no. 1065). As for bodings of good,  these used to please the Prophet (ﷺ) and so when he heard good words from  someone, he used to say: \"We have taken from you a good portent from your  mouth,\" Abu Dawud, Ahmad. See also Al-Albani, Silsilatul-'Ahadith  As-Sahihah 2/363, and it is with Abu Ash-Shaikh Al-Asfahani in  'Akhlaqun-Nabiyy, pg. 270. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: When mounting an animal or any means of transport",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 206",
    "arabic":
        " بِسْـمِ اللهِ وَالْحَمْـدُ لله، ﴿سُبْحَانَ الَّذِي سَخَّرَ لَنَا هَذَا وَمَا كُنَّا لَهُ مُقْرِنِينَ * وَإِنَّا إِلَى رَبِّنَا لَمُنقَلِبُونَ﴾ الحَمْـدُ لله، الحَمْـدُ لله، الحَمْـدُ لله، اللهُ أكْـبَر، اللهُ أكْـبَر، اللهُ أكْـبَر،  سُـبْحانَكَ اللّهُـمَّ إِنّي ظَلَـمْتُ نَفْسي فَاغْـفِرْ لي، فَإِنَّهُ لا يَغْفِـرُ الذُّنوبَ إِلاّ أَنْـت",
    "english":
        "Bismillāh,  walḥamdulillāh.  Subḥāna ‘lladhī sakhkhara lanā hādhā wa mā kunnā lahu muqrinīn.  Wa innā ilā Rabbinā lamunqalibūn.  Alḥamdulillāh, alḥamdulillāh, alḥamdulillāh,  Allāhu Akbar, Allāhu Akbar, Allāhu Akbar,  Subḥānaka ‘llāhumma innī ẓalamtu nafsī,  faghfir lī,  fa innahu lā yaghfirudh-dhunūba illā ant.\n\n With the Name of Allah.  Praise is to Allah.  Glory is to Him Who has provided this for us though we could never have had it by our efforts.  Surely, unto our Lord, we are returning. Praise is to Allah. Praise is to Allah. Praise is to Allah.  Allah is the Most Great. Allah is the Most  Great. Allah is the Most Great.  Glory is to You. O Allah, I have wronged my own soul.  Forgive me,  for surely none forgives sins but You.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 3/34, At-Tirmidhi 5/501. See also Al-Albani, Sahih  At-Tirmidhi3/156. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For travel",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 207",
    "arabic":
        " \"اللَّهُ أَكْبَرُ، اللَّهُ أَكْبَرُ، اللَّهُ أَكْبَرُ، ﴿سُبْحَانَ الَّذِي سَخَّرَ لَنَا هَذَا وَمَا كُنَّا لَهُ مُقْرِنِينَ * وَإِنَّا إِلَى رَبِّنَا لَمُنقَلِبُونَ﴾ اللَّهُمَّ إِنّا نَسْأَلُكَ فِي سَفَرِنَا هَذَا البِرَّ وَالتَّقْوَى، وَمِنَ الْعَمَلِ مَا تَرْضَى، اللَّهُمَّ هَوِّنْ عَلَيْنَا سَفَرَنَا هَذَا وَاطْوِ عَنَّا بُعْدَهُ، اللَّهُمَّ أَنْتَ الصَّاحِبُ فِي السَّفَرِ، وَالْخَليفَةُ فِي الْأَهْلِ، اللَّهُمَّ إِنِّي أَعُوذُ بِكَ مِنْ وَعْثَاءِ السَّفَرِ، وَكَآبَةِ الْمَنْظَرِ، وَسُوءِ الْمُنْقَلَبِ فِي الْمَالِ وَالْأَهْلِ\"، وإذا رَجَعَ قَالَهُنَّ وَزَادَ فِيهِنَّ: \"آيِبُونَ، تائِبُونَ، عَابِدُونَ، لِرَبِّنَا حَامِدُونَ\".",
    "english":
        "Allāhu Akbar, Allāhu Akbar, Allāhu Akbar,  Subḥāna ‘l-ladhi sakhkhara lanā hādhā  wa mā kunnā lahu muqrinīn.  Wa innā ilā Rabbinā lamunqalibūn.  Allāhumma innā nas'aluka fī safarinā hādha ‘l-birra wat-taqwā,  Wa mina ‘l-`amali mā tarḍā,  Allāhumma hawwin `alaynā safaranā hādhā waṭwi `annā bu`dah,  Allāhumma antas-sāḥibu fis-safar,  wa ‘l-khalīfatu fil-ahl,  Allāhumma innī a`ūdhu bika min wa`thā'is-safar,  wa ka'ābati ‘l-manẓar,  wa sū'il-munqalabi fil-māli wa ‘l-ahl.\n\n(Upon returning recite the same again adding): Ā’ibūna, tā'ibūna, `ābidūn,  Li Rabbinā ḥāmidūn.\n\n Allah is the Most Great. Allah is the Most Great. Allah is the Most Great.  Glory is to Him Who has provided this for us though we could never have had it by our efforts.  Surely, unto our Lord we are returning.  O Allah, we ask You on this our journey for goodness and piety,  and for works that are pleasing to You.  O Allah, lighten this journey for us and make its distance easy for us.  O Allah, You are our Companion on the road and the One in Whose care we leave our family.  O Allah, I seek refuge in You from this journey's hardships, and from the wicked sights in store  and from finding our family and property in misfortune upon returning.\n\n(Upon returning recite the same again adding :)\n\nWe return repentant to our Lord, worshipping our Lord, and praising our Lord.\n\nReference: Muslim 2/978. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon entering a town or village",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 208",
    "arabic":
        " أللّـهُمَّ رَبَّ السَّـمواتِ السّـبْعِ وَما أَظْلَلَـن، وَرَبَّ الأَراضيـنَ السّـبْعِ وَما أقْلَلْـن، وَرَبَّ الشَّيـاطينِ وَما أَضْلَلْـن، وَرَبَّ الرِّياحِ وَما ذَرَيْـن، أَسْـأَلُـكَ خَيْـرَ هذهِ الْقَـرْيَةِ وَخَيْـرَ أَهْلِـها، وَخَيْـرَ ما فيها، وَأَعـوذُ بِكَ مِنْ شَـرِّها وَشَـرِّ أَهْلِـها، وَشَـرِّ ما فيها",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma Rabbas-samāwātis-sab`i wa mā aẓlaln,  Wa Rabba ‘l-arāḍīnas-sab`i wa mā aqlaln,  wa Rabbash-shayāṭīni wa mā aḍlaln,  wa Rabbar-riyāḥi wa mā dharayn.  As'aluka khayra hādhihi ‘l-qaryah,  wa khayra ahlihā,  wa khayra māfīhā,  wa a`ūdhu bika min sharrihā,  wa sharri ahlihā,  wa sharri mā fīhā.\n\n O Allah, Lord of the seven heavens and all they overshadow, Lord of the seven worlds and all they uphold,  Lord of the devils and all they lead astray, Lord of the winds and all they scatter.  I ask You for the goodness of this town,  and for the goodness of its people,  and for the goodness it contains.  I seek refuge in You from its evil,  from the evil of its people,  and from the evil it contains.\n\nReference: Al-Hakim who graded it authentic and Ath-Tfaahabi agreed 2/100, and Ibn  As-Sunni (no. 524). Al-Hafidh graded it good in his checking of Al-'Athkdr  5/154. Ibn Baz said in Tuhfatul-'Akhydr p. 37, that An-Nasa'i recorded it  with a good chain of narration. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: When entering the market",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 209",
    "arabic":
        " لا إلهَ إلاّ اللّه وحدَهُ لا شريكَ لهُ، لهُ المُلْـكُ ولهُ الحَمْـد،  يُحْيـي وَيُميـتُ وَهُوَ حَيٌّ لا يَمـوت، بِيَـدِهِ الْخَـيْرُ وَهوَ على كلّ شيءٍ قدير",
    "english":
        "Lā ilāha illallāh waḥdahu lā sharīka lah,  Lahu ‘l-mulku wa lahu ‘l-ḥamd,  Yuḥyī wa yumīt,  wa huwa ḥayyun lā yamūt, Biyadihi ‘l-khayr,  wa huwa `alā kulli shay'in Qadīr.\n\n None has the right to be worshipped but Allah alone,  Who has no partner. His is the dominion and His is the praise. He brings life and He causes death,  and He is living and does not die.  In His Hand is all good,  and He is Able to do all things.\n\nReference: At-Tirmidhi 5/291, and Al-Hakim 1/538. Al-Albani graded it good in Sahih  Ibn Majah 2/21 and Sahih At-Tirmidhi 3/152. "
  },
