  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Prayer of the traveller as dawn approaches",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 215",
    "arabic":
        " سَمِـعَ سـامِعٌ بِحَمْـدِ اللهِ وَحُسْـنِ بَلائِـهِ عَلَيْـنا. رَبَّنـا صـاحِبْـنا وَأَفْـضِل عَلَيْـنا  عائِذاً باللهِ مِنَ النّـار",
    "english":
        "Sami`a sāmi`un biḥamdillāhi wa ḥusni balā'ihi `alaynā.  Rabbanā ṣāḥibnā, wa afḍil `alaynā,  `ā'idhan billāhi minan-nār.\n\n He Who listens has heard that we praise Allah for the good things He gives us.  Our Lord, be with us and bestow Your favor upon us.  I seek the protection of Allah from the Fire.\n\nReference: Muslim 4/2086, the meaning of sami`a sāmi`un (who listens has heard) is  that 'a witness has witnessed our praise of Allah due to His blessings and  favor upon us.' It could also be read samma`a sāmi`un, in which case it  means 'one who has heard this statement of mine will convey it to another  and he will say it as well.' This is due to the attention given to the  Thikr (remembrance of Allah) and supplications made during the early  morning hours. The meaning of his saying 'Our Lord, be with us and bestow  Your favor upon us' is: 'Our Lord, protect us and guard us. Bless us with  Your numerous bounties, and avert from us every evil.' See An-Nawawi, Sharh  Sahih Muslim 17/39. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Stopping or lodging somewhere in travel and otherwise",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 216",
    "arabic": " أَعـوذُ بِكَلِـماتِ اللّهِ التّـامّاتِ مِنْ شَـرِّ ما خَلَـق",
    "english":
        "A`ūdhu bikalimāti ‘llāhit-tāmmāti min sharri mā khalaq.\n\nI seek refuge in the Perfect Words of Allah from the evil of what He has created.\n\nReference: Muslim 4/2080. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: While returning from travel",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 217",
    "arabic":
        " يُكَبِّرُ عَلَى كُلِّ شَرَفٍ ثَلاَثَ تَكْبِيرَاتٍ ثُمَّ يَقُولُ:  لاَ إِلَهَ إِلاَّ اللَّهُ  وَحْدَهُ لاَ شَرِيكَ لَهُ،  لَهُ الْمُلْكُ، وَلَهُ الْحَمْدُ،  وَهُوَ عَلَى كُلِّ شَيْءٍ قَدِيرٌ،  آيِبُونَ، تَائِبُونَ، عَابِدُونَ،  لِرَبِّنا حَامِدُونَ،  صَدَقَ اللَّهُ وَعْدَهُ،  وَنَصَرَ عَبْدَهُ،  وَهَزَمَ الْأَحْزابَ وَحْدَهُ",
    "english":
        "From every elevated point say  Allāhu Akbar (three times),  and then recite:\n\nLā ilāha illallāh  waḥdahu lā sharīka lah,  lahu ‘l-mulku, walahu ‘l-ḥamd,  wa Huwa `alā kulli shay'in Qadīr,  ā'ibūna, tā'ibūna,`ābidūn,  li Rabbinā ḥāmidūn,  sadaqallāhu wa`dah,  wa nasara `abdah, wa hazama ‘l-'aḥzāba waḥdah.\n\n From every elevated point say Allāhu Akbar (Allah is the Most Great) three times and then recite:\n\nNone has the right to be worshipped but Allah alone,  Who has no partner.  His is the dominion and His is the praise, and He is Able to do all things.  We return repentant to our Lord, worshipping our Lord,  and praising our Lord.  He fulfilled His Promise,  He aided His slave,  and He alone defeated the Confederates.\n\nReference: Bukhari 7/163, Muslim 2/980. The Prophet (ﷺ) used to say this when  returning from a campaign or from Hajj. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: What to say upon receiving pleasing or displeasing news",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 218",
    "arabic":
        " كَانَ النَّبِيُّ صلى الله عليه وسلم إِذَا أَتَاهُ الْأَمْرُ يَسُرُّهُ قَالَ: (الْحَمْدُ لِلَّهِ الَّذِي بِنِعْمَتِهِ تَتِمُّ الصَّالِحَاتُ) وَإِذَا أَتَاهُ الْأَمْرُ يَكْرَهُهُ قَالَ: (الْحَمْدُ لِلَّهِ عَلَى كُلِّ حَالٍ)",
    "english":
        "When something happened that pleased him, the Prophet (ﷺ) used to say: Alḥamdu lillāhi ‘lladhi bi ni`matihi tatimmuṣ-ṣāliḥāt. And if something happened that displeased him, he used to say: Alḥamdu lillāhi `alā kulli ḥāl.\n\n When something happened that pleased him, the Prophet (ﷺ) used to say: Praise is to Allah Who by His blessings all good things are perfected.\n\nAnd if something happened that displeased him, he used to say: Praise is to Allah in all circumstances.\n\nReference: Ibn As-Sunni, 'Amalul-Yawm wal-Laylah, and Al-Hakim who graded it authentic  1/499. See also Al-Albani, Sahihul-Jami' As-Saghir 4/201. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Excellence of sending prayers upon the Prophet (saws)",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 219",
    "arabic":
        " قَالَ النَّبِيُّ صلى الله عليه وسلم: (مَنْ صَلَّى عَلَيَّ صَلاَةً صَلَّى اللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ بِهَا عَشْراً)",
    "english":
        "--\n\nThe Prophet (ﷺ) said: \"Whoever prays for Allah's blessings upon me once, will be blessed for it by Allah ten times.\"\n\nReference: Muslim 1/288. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Excellence of sending prayers upon the Prophet (saws)",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 220",
    "arabic":
        " وَقَالَ صلى الله عليه وسلم: (لاَ تَجْعَلُوا قَبْرِي عِيداً وَصَلُّوا عَلَيَّ؛ فَإِنَّ صَلاَتَكُم تَبْلُغُنِي حَيْثُ كُنْتُمْ)",
    "english":
        "--\n\nThe Prophet (ﷺ) said: \"Do not make my grave a place of ritual celebration, but pray for Allah's blessings upon me, for your blessings reach me from wherever you are.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 2/218, Ahmad 2/367. Al-Albani graded it authentic in Sahih Abu  Dawud 2/383. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Excellence of sending prayers upon the Prophet (saws)",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 221",
    "arabic":
        " وَقَالَ صلى الله عليه وسلم: (الْبَخِيلُ مَنْ ذُكِرْتُ عِنْدَهُ فَلَمْ يُصَلِّ عَلَيَّ)",
    "english":
        "--\n\nThe Prophet (ﷺ) said: \"The miser is the one in whose presence I am mentioned yet does not pray for Allah's blessings upon me.\"\n\nReference: At-Tirmidhi 5/551 and others. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmidhi 3/177  and Sahihul-Jarai' As-Saghir 3/25. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Excellence of sending prayers upon the Prophet (saws)",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 222",
    "arabic":
        " وَقَالَ صلى الله عليه وسلم:(إِنَّ لِلَّهِ مَلاَئِكَةً سَيَّاحِينَ فِي الْأَرْضِ يُبَلِّغُونِي مِنْ أُمَّتِي السَّلاَمَ)",
    "english":
        "--\n\nThe Prophet (ﷺ) said: \"Indeed Allah has angels who roam the earth and they convey to me the greetings (or prayers of peace) of my Ummah (nation).\"\n\nReference: An-Nasa'i, Al-Hakim 2/421. Al-Albani graded it authentic in Sahih An-Nasa'i  1/274. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Excellence of sending prayers upon the Prophet (saws)",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 223",
    "arabic":
        " وَقَالَ صلى الله عليه وسلم: (مَا مِنْ أَحَدٍ يُسَلِّمُ عَلَيَّ إِلاَّ رَدَّ اللَّهُ عَلَيَّ رُوحِيَ حَتَّى أَرُدَّ عَلَيْهِ السَّلاَمَ)",
    "english":
        "--\n\nThe Prophet (ﷺ) said: \"No one sends greetings (or prayers of peace) upon me but Allah returns my soul to me so that I may return his greetings.\"\n\nReference: Abu Dawud (no. 2041). Al-Albani graded it good in Sahih Abu Dawud 1/383. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Excellence of spreading the Islamic greeting",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 224",
    "arabic":
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم: (لاَ تَدْخُلُوا الْجَنَّةَ حَتَّى تُؤْمِنُوا، وَلاَ تُؤْمِنُوا حَتَّى تَحَابُّوا، أَوَلاَ أَدُلُّكُم عَلَى شَيْءٍ إِذَا فَعَلْتُمُوهُ تَحَابَبْتُم، أَفْشُوا السَّلاَمَ بَيْنَكُمْ)",
    "english":
        "--\n\nThe Prophet (ﷺ) said: \"You shall not enter Paradise until you believe, and you have not believed until you love one another. Shall I tell you of something you can do to make you love one another? Spread the greetings of Salam (peace) amongst yourselves (i.e. between each other).\n\nReference: Muslim 1/74 and others. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Excellence of spreading the Islamic greeting",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 225",
    "arabic":
        " ثَلاَثٌ مَنْ جَمَعَهُنَّ فَقَدْ جَمَعَ الْإِيمَانَ: الْإِنْصَافُ مِنْ نَفْسِكَ، وَبَذْلُ السَّلاَمِ لِلْعَالَمِ، وَالْإِنْفَاقُ مِنَ الإِقْتَارِ",
    "english":
        "Three characteristics, whoever combines them, has completed his faith: to be just, to spread greetings to all people and to spend (charitably) out of the little you have.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, cf. Al-Asqalani, Fathul-Bari 1/82 as a statement of the  Companion 'Ammar (RA). "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Excellence of spreading the Islamic greeting",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 226",
    "arabic":
        " وَعَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عُمَرَ رَضِيَ اللَّهُ عَنْهُمَا: أنَّ رَجُلاً سَأَلَ النَّبِيَّ صلى الله عليه وسلم أيُّ الْإِسْلاَمِ خَيْرٌ قَالَ: (تُطْعِمُ الطَّعَامَ، وَتَقْرأُ السَّلاَمَ عَلَى مَنْ عَرَفْتَ وَمَنْ لَمْ تَعْرِفْ)",
    "english":
        "--\n\n`Abdullah bin `Umar (RA) said: A man asked the Prophet (ﷺ), \"What is the best act of Islam?\" He said, \"To feed others and to give greetings of Salam (peace) to those whom you know and to those whom you do not know. \"\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, cf. Al-Asqalani, Fathul-Bari 1/55, Muslim 1/65. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Returning a greeting to a disbeliever",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 227",
    "arabic":
        " إذَا سَلَّمَ عَلَيْكُمْ أَهْلُ الْكِتَابِ فَقُولُوا: وَعَلَيْكُمْ",
    "english":
        "If one of the People of the Scripture (i.e. Christians and Jews) greets you, saying As-Salāmu `alaykum, then say (to him): Wa `alaykum.\n\nIf one of the People of the Scripture (i.e. Christians and Jews) greets you saying As-Salaamu `alaykum, then say (to him):\n\nAnd upon you .\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, cf. Al-Asqalani, Fathul-Bari 11/42, Muslim 4/1705. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon hearing a rooster crow or the braying of a donkey",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 228",
    "arabic":
        " إِذَا سَمِعْتُمْ صِيَاحَ الدِّيَكَةِ فَاسْأَلُوا اللَّهَ مِنْ فَضْلِهِ؛ فَإِنَّهَا رَأَتْ مَلَكاً وَإِذَا سَمِعْتُمْ نَهِيقَ الْحِمَارِ فَتَعَوَّذُوا بِاللَّهِ مِنَ الشَّيطَانِ؛ فَإِنَّهُ رَأَى شَيْطَاناً",
    "english":
        "--\n\nWhen you hear the cock's crow, ask Allah for His favor upon you for surely it has seen an angel. When you hear the bray of a donkey, seek refuge in Allah from Satan, for surely it has seen a devil.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, cf. Al-Asqalani, Fathul-Bari 6/350, Muslim 4/2092. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Upon hearing the barking of dogs at night",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 229",
    "arabic":
        " إِذَا سَمِعْتُمْ نُبَاحَ الْكِلاَبِ وَنَهِيقَ الْحَمِيرِ بِاللَّيْلِ فَتَعَوَّذُوا بِاللَّهِ مِنْهُنَّ؛ فَإِنَّهُنَّ يَرَيْنَ مَا لاَ تَرَوْنَ",
    "english":
        "\n\nWhen you hear a dog barking or a donkey braying in the night, then seek refuge in Allah from them, for surely they have seen what you see not.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 4/327, Ahmad 3/306. Al-Albani graded it authentic in Sahih Abu  Dawud 3/961. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For one you have insulted",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 230",
    "arabic":
        " قال صلى الله عليه وسلم: \"اللَّهُم فأيما مؤمن سببته فاجعل ذلك له قربة إليك يوم القيامة\"",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma fa'ayyumā mu'minin sababtuhu  faj`al dhālika lahu qurbatan ilayka yawma ‘l-qiyāmah.\n\n O Allah, whomever of the believers I have abused, give him the reward of a sacrificial slaughter for it on the Day of Resurrection.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, cf. Al-Asqalani, Fathul-Bari 11/171, Muslim 4/2007. The wording  in Muslim's report is: 'make it a purification for him and a source of  mercy. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: The etiquette of praising a fellow Muslim",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 231",
    "arabic":
        " قال صلى الله عليه وسلم: \"إِذَا كَانَ أَحَدُكُم مَادِحاً صَاحِبَهُ لاَ مَحَالَةَ فَلْيَقُلْ: أَحْسِبُ فُلاَناً وَاللَّهُ حَسِيبُهُ، وَلاَ أُزَكِّي عَلَى اللَّهِ أَحَداً، أَحْسِبُهُ – إِنْ كَانَ يَعْلَمُ ذَاكَ – كَذَا وَكَذَا\"",
    "english":
        "If any of you praises his companion then let him say: Aḥsibu fulānan wallāhu ḥasībuh wa lā uzakkī  `alallāhi aḥada.\n\n If any of you praises his companion then let him say: I consider (such and such a person), and Allah is his Assessor, (meaning: and I cannot claim anyone to be pious before Allah) if you know of this (good character trait in the person) to be such and such (saying what he thinks is praiseworthy in that person).\n\nReference: Muslim 4/2296. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: For the one that have been praised",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 232",
    "arabic":
        "اللَّهُمَّ لاَ تُؤَاخِذْنِي بِمَا يَقُولُونَ وَاغْفِرْ لِي مَا لاَ يَعْلَمُونَ  [وَاجْعَلْنِي خَيْرًا مِمَّا يَظُّنُّونَ]",
    "english":
        "Allāhumma lā tu'ākhidhnī bimā yaqūlūn,  waghfir lī mā lā ya`lamūn [waj`alnī khayran mimmā yaẓunnūn].\n\n O Allah, do not call me to account for what they say and forgive me for what they have no knowledge of  [and make me better than they imagine].\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, Al-'Adabul-Mufrad no. 761. See Al-Albani, Sahih  Al-'Adabul-Mufrad (no. 585). The portion between brackets if from  Al-Bayhaqi, Shu'ab Al-Iman 4/228, and comes another account. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: The Talbiya for the one doing Hajj or 'Umrah",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 233",
    "arabic":
        " لَبَّيْكَ اللَّهُمَّ لَبَّيْكَ،  لَبَّيْكَ لاَ شَرِيكَ لَكَ لَبَّيْكَ،  إِنَّ الْحَمْدَ والنِّعْمَة لَكَ والمُلْكُ،  لَا شَرِيكَ لَكَ",
    "english":
        "Labbayk-Allāhumma labbayk,  labbayka lā sharīka laka labbayk, inna ‘l-ḥamda, wanni`mata, laka wa ‘l-mulk,  lā sharīka lak.\n\n I am here at Your service, O Allah, I am here at Your service.  I am here at Your service, You have no partner, I am here at Your service.  Surely the praise, and blessings are Yours, and the dominion.  You have no partner.\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, cf. Al-Asqalani, Fathul-Bari 3/408, Muslim 2/841. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: The Takbîr passing the black stone",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 234",
    "arabic":
        " طَافَ النَّبيُّ صلى الله عليه وسلم بِالْبَيْتِ عَلَى بَعِيرٍ كُلَّمَا أَتَى الرُّكْنَ أَشَارَ إِلَيْهِ بِشَيْءٍ عِنْدَهُ وَكَبَّرَ",
    "english":
        "--\n\nThe Prophet (ﷺ) performed Tawaf riding a camel. Every time he passed the corner (containing the Black Stone), he would point to it with something that he was holding and say: Allāhu Akbar (Allah is the Most Great)!\n\nReference: Al-Bukhari, cf. Al-Asqalani, Fathul-Bari 3/476. See also 472. The  'something' that was referred to in this Hadith was a cane. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: Between the Yemeni corner and the black stone",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 235",
    "arabic":
        " ﴿رَبَّنَا آتِنَا في الدُّنْيَا حسَنَةً وفي الآخِرَةِ حسَنةً  وقِنَا عذَابَ النَّارِ﴾",
    "english":
        "Rabbanā ātinā fid-dunyā ḥasanah  wa fi ‘l-ākhirati ḥasanah  wa qinā `adhāban-nār.\n\n Our Lord, grant us the good things in this world, and the good things in the next life, and save us from the punishment of the Fire.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 2/179, Ahmad 3/411, Al-Baghawi, Sharhus-Sunnah 7/128. Al-Albani  graded it good in Sahih Abu Dawud 1/354. The Ayat is from Surat Al-Baqarah,  2:201. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: When at Mount Safa and Mount Marwah",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 236",
    "arabic":
        " (لَمَّا دَنَا النَّبِيُّ صلى الله عليه وسلم مِنَ الصَّفَا قَرَأَ: ﴿إِنَّ الصَّفَا وَالْمَرْوَةَ مِنْ شَعَآئِرِ اللَّهِ﴾ \"أَبْدَأُ بِمَا بَدَأَ اللَّهُ بِهِ\" فَبَدَأَ بِالصَّفَا فَرَقِيَ عَلَيْهِ حَتَّى رَأَى الْبَيْتَ، فَاسْتَقْبَلَ الْقِبْلَةَ، فَوَحَّدَ اللَّهَ وَكبَّرَهُ وَقَالَ: لاَ إِلَهَ إِلاَّ اللَّهُ وَحْدَهُ لاَ شَرِيكَ لَهُ، لَهُ الْمُلْكُ وَلَهُ الْحَمْدُ وَهُوَ عَلَى كُلِّ شَيْءٍ قَدِيرٌ، لاَ إِلَهَ إِلاَّ اللَّهُ وَحْدَهُ، أَنْجَزَ وَعْدَهُ، وَنَصَرَ عَبْدَهُ، وَهَزَمَ الْأَحْزَابَ وَحْدَهُ، ثُمَّ دَعَا بَيْنَ ذلكَ. قَالَ مِثْلَ هَذَا ثَلاَثَ مَرَّاتٍ) الْحَدِيثُ. وَفِيهِ: (فَفَعَلَ عَلَى الْمَرْوَةِ كَمَا فَعَلَ عَلَى الصَّفَا)",
    "english":
        "Whenever the Prophet (ﷺ) approached Mount Safa, he would recite: Innaṣ-Ṣafā wa ‘l-Marwata min sha`ā'irillāh.  Abda'u bimā bada'allāhu bih. He began (his Sa`y) at Mount Safa climbing it, until he could see the House. He then faced the Qiblah repeating the words: Lā ilāha illallāh, Allāhu Akbar Then he said: Lā ilāha 'illallāh waḥdahu lā sharīka lah,  Lahu ‘l-mulku wa lahu ‘l-ḥamd wa Huwa `alā kulli shay'in Qadīr,  lā 'ilāha illallāhu waḥdahu,  anjaza wa`dahu, wa naṣara `abdahu,  wa hazama ‘l 'aḥzāba waḥdah. Then he would ask Allah for what he liked, repeating the same three times. He did at Mount Marwah as he did at Mount Safa.\n\nWhenever the Prophet (ﷺ) approached Mount Safa, he would recite:\n\nSurely Safa and Marwah are among the signs of Allah. I begin by that which Allah began.\n\nHe began (his Sa'y) at Mount Safa climbing it until he could see the House. He then faced the Qiblah repeating the words:\n\nThere is none worthy of worship but Allah, and Allah is the Most Great.\n\nThen he said:\n\nNone has the right to be worshipped but Allah alone, Who has no partner, His is the dominion and His is the praise, and He is Able to do all things. None has the right to be worshipped but Allah alone, He fulfilled His Promise, He aided His slave, and He alone defeated Confederates.\n\nThen he would ask Allah for what he liked, repeating the same thing like this three times. He did at Mount Marwah as he did at Mount Safa.\n\nReference: Muslim 2/888. "
  },
  {
    "title": "Chapter: The Day of 'Arafah",
    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 237",
    "arabic":
        " خير الدعاء دعاء يوم عرفة ، وخيرُ ما قلت أنا والنبيُّون من قبلي : لا إله إلا الله وحدهُ لا شريك لهُ ، لهُ الملكُ ولهُ الحمدُ وهو على كل شيء قدير.",
    "english":
        "The Prophet (ﷺ) said: The best invocation is that of the Day of Arafat, and the best that anyone can say is what I and the Prophets before me have said:\n\nLā 'ilāha 'illallāhu  waḥdahu lā sharīka lahu,  lahul-mulku wa lahul-ḥamdu  wa huwa `alā kulli shay'in qadīr.\n\nNone has the right to be worshipped but Allah  Alone, Who has no partner.  His is the dominion and His is the praise, and He is Able to do all things.\n\nReference: At-Tirmidhi. Al-Albani graded it good in Sahih At-Tirmidhi 3/184, and also  Silsilatul-'Ahadith As-Sahihah 4/6. "
  },
  {
