    "reference": "Reference : Hisn al-Muslim 250",
    "arabic":
        " وَقَالَ صلى الله عليه وسلم: مَنْ قَالَ (أَسْتَغْفِرُ اللَّهَ الْعَظيمَ الَّذِي لاَ إِلَهَ إِلاَّ هُوَ الْحَيُّ القَيّوُمُ وَأَتُوبُ إِلَيهِ)، غَفَرَ اللَّهُ لَهُ وَإِنْ كَانَ فَرَّ مِنَ الزَّحْفِ.",
    "english":
        "Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) said: Whoever says: Astaghfirullāha ‘l-'Aẓīm alladhi lā ilāha illā huwa ‘l-ḥayyul-Qayyūm  wa atūbu ilayh.\n\n Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) said: Whoever says:\n\nI seek the forgiveness of Allah the Mighty, Whom there is none worthy of worship except Him, the Living, the Eternal,  and I repent to Him,  Allah will forgive him even if he has deserted the army's ranks.\n\nReference: Abu Dawud 2/85, At-Tirmidhi 5/569, and Al-Hakim who declared it authentic  and Ath-Thahabi agreed with him 1/511. Al-Albani graded it authentic in  Sahih At-Tirmidhi 3/182. See also Jami'ul-'Usool li-'Ahdaith Ar-Rasool 4/  389-90 checked by Al-Arna'ut. "
  },
  {
